Former NPA boss Mxolisi Nxasana says the fact that none of the NPA heads finished their terms of office point to political interference. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Former NPA boss Mxolisi Nxasana has named his then deputy Nomgcobo Jiba in the campaign to remove him from the NPA. Nxasana is testifying before the State Capture Inquiry. READ: Nxasana: There has been political interference at NPA He was head of the prosecuting authority from 2013 and in 2015 he stepped down with a multimillion-rand golden handshake. Nxasana said the fact that none of the NPA heads finished their terms of office points to political interference. He has also slammed the conduct of his then deputy Nomgcobo Jiba in the case involving former KZN Hawks Head Johan Booysen. READ: Jiba, Mrwebi fired Nxasana has been asked not to give new evidence implicating Jiba until further notice. Her lawyer Vuyani Ngalwana says his client wasn't notified that she'll be implicated by Nxasana.